RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 61. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: REDZILLA led the field while saving ground around the first turn, dueled on the inside up the backstretch and around the second bend and kicked clear in the stretch. RIPLEY EFFECT raced in the middle of the pack between horses through the opening half mile, began a bid from the three path coming around the far turn and could not go with the winner in the stretch but chased that rival home. TIPHARAH saved ground around the first turn, tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the far bend in the three path and kept on to the wire. FIRST FAITH raced in the three path early, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the two path coming around the far turn and finished evenly. PATH TO VICTORY raced off the pace on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, began to move up from the four path coming around the second bend and was outkicked in the lane. JOYOUS FAIRY TALE raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the two path and faded in the stretch. BLACK KARMA raced in the two path around the first bend, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the inside, dropped back to trail the field while saving ground around the second turn and was empty from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 2 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 78. Maiden Special Weight Purse 32000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $25,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $25,000 And Since Then Have Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $25,000 Or More.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROYAL DAME raced in the four path around the first turn, chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the second turn and kicked clear in the stretch. PATIENCE WORTH led the field from the two path around the first turn, continued to show the way racing inside up the backstretch, dueled while saving ground around the far bend, gave way in upper stretch and chased the winner home from there. JET CITY WOMAN hit the gate leaving it, raced off the pace in the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, began a bid from the three and four path headed into the far turn and finished evenly. MACHIAVELLIQUE fought her rider while racing in the three path around the first turn, settled down to trail the field up the backstretch, navigated the second bend from the two path and never threatened. REKINDLED raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the inside, began to tire quickly while saving ground around the far turn and was eased in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 3 1 1/16M Turf CR: 68. Maiden Claiming Purse 18500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000 (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $25,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $25,000 And Since Then Have Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $25,000 Or More.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROMANTIC FANTASY raced in the two path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace, began a bid from the three and four path coming around the far turn and gained ground to kick clear late. PARTY DREAM raced at the back of the pack on the inside through the opening half mile, navigated the far turn from the two path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground late. SHE'S SO BEARRISH dueled while saving ground around the first turn, led the way on the inside up the backstretch and around the second bend, was clear in upper stretch and was collared in the final furlong. TIZ A TEMPEST raced in the two path early, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, began to move up while racing in the three path around the far turn and continued to improve position in the lane. SARA KALI dueled from the two path around the first turn, dropped back to chase the leader on the outside up the backstretch and around the far bend and weakened in the stretch. UNCAPTURED DREAMS raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the inside, raced into traffic and bobbled slightly in the two path coming around the far turn and never threatened. RISKY TIZZY was away from the gate a bit slowly, saved ground around the first turn, raced at the back of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the second bend in the two path and made no bid. IMAZETA saved ground early, trailed the field up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn and was never a factor. THE RIDER OF HORSE FOUR, UNCAPTURED DREAMS, CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST HORSE THREE, TIZ A TEMPEST, CITING INTERFERENCE AROUND THE FAR TURN. UPON REVIEW, NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb. (Registered Florida Breds Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SWILL MERCHANT stumbled slightly and brushed with the horse to his outside leaving the gate, recovered to lead the way up the backstretch, dueled while saving ground around the turn and kicked clear in the stretch. SUNSPOT stalked the leader on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, began a bid from the three path coming around the bend and chased on in the lane. NOT A DANCE raced off the pace up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three path, launched a bid passing the quarter pole and improved position in the stretch. RECTANGLE stumbled mildly leaving the gate, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and improved position mildly in the lane. ANDY WALKS WITH ME tracked the pace setters on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the turn and weakened in the stretch. DOC CARSON raced in the middle of the pack on the outside early, navigated the bend from the four path and faded from there. RED JET trailed well behind the field up the backstretch and while saving ground around the turn and made up some ground in the stretch but never threatened. HEAVY WEIGHT bumped lightly with the horse to his inside at the start, pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the two path and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 5 1M Turf CR: 83. Maiden Claiming Purse 18500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000 (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $25,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $25,000 And Since Then Hav e Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $25,000 Or More.). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CRAFTY KING raced in the five path around the first turn, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the far turn and gained ground to get up for the win late. WHISKEYMAC raced in the four path around the first turn, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the second turn, dueled in the lane and was caught late. BALLINDINE pressed the pace from the three path through the opening half mile, dueled from the two path around the far turn and in upper stretch and gave way in the final sixteenth of a mile. FIRE BARON saved ground around the first turn, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the second bend from the four path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground in late stretch. COPAZO tracked the leader from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the second turn in the three path and was outkicked in the lane. ALL ABOUT LUCKY led the field while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled from the rail coming around the far bend, lugged in and hit the rail in upper stretch and tired from there. THIRD DEGREE raced in the two path around the first turn, trailed the field up the backstretch, switched to the four and five path for the run around the second turn and passed tiring horses in the stretch. TURESKIS raced at the pack of the pack on the outside through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn in the three path and made no bid. MO TOWN BLUES raced into traffic from the three path headed around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the far bend and faded in the lane. THE BEARRISH ONE saved ground around the first turn, raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the second turn and was empty from there. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THE INCIDENT IN UPPER STRETCH. UPON REVIEW, NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

SWIFT KID trailed the field from the two path through the opening half mile, began a bid from the five path coming around the far turn and gained ground late. BAM BAM WARRIOR raced in the three path around the first turn, continued in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far turn still in the three path and improved position in the lane. CEDAR BEACH raced in the four path early, tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, dropped back while racing in the four path around the far bend and continued to fade in the stretch. SANDY DUDE saved ground around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace between horses, came around the second turn in the three path and made no bid. MARCEL saved ground around the first turn, led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dropped back while racing on the rail around the far turn and continued to tire from there. GIOVANE'S PROMISE saved ground in the middle of the pack around the first turn and up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the far turn and was empty in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 8 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 94. Claiming Purse 17000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since January 4 Allowed 2 lbs. GOLDEN TONE raced in the two path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the second turn and dueled to the wire but could not get by the winner.
